Project CODERUNNER - Version Two - 24 Mar 2026

This is a CGI FORM for running Code. Languages supported include: 

    Bash
    PHP
    Perl
    Ruby
    Python
    Gcc
    Lua
    Rust

Others can be added at will.

There are literally dozens of online code running websites. Why one more?

This is 1,000 lines of Bash and is for LOCALHOST.

Notes

I code in a really abusive style. Very little commenting but if you do not 
understand the code than I am doing something wrong...

(I use trailing ellipses as a comment, meaning, "this may be wrong", but also, 
"more here later". *sigh*)

The code is split into "modules" with three-letter names:

   BAS          some basic functions everyone needs
   BIN          the language binaries
   CFG          configuration
   HTM          the HTML
   QRY          the Server Query data
   SRV          the Server data

And one oddball:

   DIAG         for the diagnostic debugger thing I created which is separate

I call this an "Experiment" for I am trying to write code that is all DATA 
and tiny, little (redundant) algorithms that manipulate that DATA, trying to 
not program in any traditional way...

The code is (trying to be) self-configuring. (I also say that the code is self-
documenting, but it is not by the typical definition of self-documenting code. 
Sorry, I will not comform.)

Adding a Language

In the BIN.SH module there are INI-like data for the languages; here are two:

    [gcc]
    bin gcc
    tmp c.c
    name C
    desc "C Code"
    comp 1
    [php]
    bin "php"
    tmp php.tmp
    name PHP
    desc "PHP Code"
    pre "<?php "

Just keep adding: "comp" means it's a compiled language; "pre" is used as a 
prefix added. Go it turns out is just another entry:

    [go]
    bin "go run"
    tmp tmp.go
    name Go
    desc "Go Lang"
    pre "package main;"

One just must have all the Go environment variables set.

Oh, right. The use of a input radio's for the languages is short-sighted and 
not suitable for growth...

The Colossal Debugger

Included is the Colossal Debugger, "echoe":

    function echoe {
        echo "$*"
    }

Which, when a bug is suspected, you pillferate the code with. When the bug is 
found, you do a search and delete on all the Colassal Debugger calls!

